actionHeader: Header for the action buttons table column
allowMultipleMaterials: Allows people to submit cuts with different materials but same name
allowMultiples: Allows people to submit different cuts with the same name
allowTour: Allows the LaserQueue visual tour to occur.
attrEditPerms: The tags non-authenticated users are allowed to edit with the `attr` action.
authTimeout: Timeout before authed user is deauthed
devLog: Enable in-page dev log. Disabling redirects to standard console logging.
highestPriorityAllowed: The highest priority allowed for non-auths to submit with.
host: Automatically generated by default. The WebSockets backend address.
lengthBounds: Maximum and minimum for the length of a job. Set either to -1 to disable that bound.
materials: An object of acceptable material codes and their names. See API.md for default material codes and names
metabump: Number of seconds before a metabump occurs. Set to 0 to disable.
metabumpmax: The top priority (0 is maximum) that can be bumped to. Anything below 0 will allow any priority.
metabumpmult: The extra amount of time it takes per priority to reach the next level
nameHeader: Header for job name table column
passDepth: How many jobs from the top are allowed to be passed off.
passHover: The hovertext for the pass button.
priorities: An array of priority names, from lowest to highest
priorityHeader: Header for priority column of table
priorityAllow: Allow anyone to submit at any priority.
priorityThresh: Thresholds for bumping longer jobs down
recalcPriority: Whether to recalculate priority intelligently based on job length
recapitalize: When true, names get capitalized intelligently
reconnectRate: How frequenetly to try reconnecting to the backend when connection drops
refreshRate: How often to poll for new data.
sendNotifications: Send notifications to the client whenever it causes an error on the backend
timeHeader: Header for time column in table
